   competitive markets and does not address the industry life cycle. It
   therefore implies that transaction-cost economizing is a superior firm
   strategy regardless of the stage of the life cycle. This paper seeks to
   reconcile these two streams of research by investigating whether
   aligning transactions with governance modes in accordance with
   transaction-cost prescriptions has a differential effect on firm
