AB We investigate the benefits of migrating from a call center, where all
   agents are pooled and customers are treated indifferently by any agent,
   toward a call center where customers are grouped into clusters with
   dedicated teams of agents. Each cluster is referred to as a portfolio.
   Customers of the same portfolio are always served by an agent of the
   corresponding team. There is no specialization involved in this
   organization in the sense that all customer portfolios as well as all
   agent teams have (statistically) identical behaviors. The reason for
   moving to this organization is that dealing with teams of limited size
   allows a much better workforce management than the situation usually
   encountered in large call centers.
