   like to evaluate the expected optimal value and the marginal
   distribution of the optimal solution. We call this the persistency
   problem for a discrete optimization problem under uncertain objective,
   and the marginal probability mass function of the optimal solution is
   named the persistence value. In general, this is a difficult problem to
   solve, even if the distribution of the objective coefficient is well
