   entering. In the latter deterrence strategy, the global firm transfers
   enough component technology to the emerging market, reducing the global
   firm's variable cost to make the potential imitator's revenues so low
   that it is not worthwhile entering. Which deterrence strategy the global
   firm should employ depends on the degree to which geographical proximity
   reduces imitation costs and the degree of differentiation between the
